<br>
I don't typically respond more far worse start one of these threads. I'm feeling very inspired to at least put together a few thoughts on a wizard. I realize that in most cases these thread really serve no purpose for in most cases they deter people considering a class then they help.<br>
<br>
Either way let me start my manifesto by saying I have a Raistlin complex (pardon if I misspelled). For those of you who are/not familiar with Raistlin from the Hickmand and Wies Dragonlance Chronicles Raistlin is portrayed as a reclusive wizard with an insatiable lust for power. So strong is this lust for arcane power that it has taken a physical toll on his 'material' body. <br>
<br>
When I chose a wizard as my class I envisioned Raistlin. Physically weak and rather aloof to the rest of the world. Just a man walking the world (in this case Norrath) in search of becoming the most powerful being ever. Granted not even Raistlin succeeded in his quest, but his search and is determination for power was in reality power.<br>
<br>
Getting on with it.. I remember that Hickman and Wies' portayal of Rastlin wasn't based on mana but on D&amp;D rules of course... but in reality the way they depicted the tale it would make sense in the EQ world as well. Rastlin as he cast his spells or channeled his power became phsically weak and tired. Upon the need he would unleash arcane power to the point of death. Almost anyway.<br>
<br>
My question would be that in addition to mana and as a means for attaining percentage based damage spells why can't we have stamina / health be a factor in our casting? Or perhaps like Harvest a stun of sorts that renders us incapable of much without attention of a healer or protection of a tank?<br>
<br>
Personally I love soloing, but I love grouping more. So this next statement is biased. I think bonds of force / atol's fizzel and other snare type spells shouldn't be a wizard spell. IMO. I also think that DD's shouldn't be a proc on weapons. This doesn't include stuns and poison based mind you. <br>
<br>
I also think that wizards shield spells are fine as they are if nothing else too strong. However, I do think that wizards should be an EXTREMELY feared class and today they are not. Start the fix by creating a low aggro series of nukes / rains that 'funnel' the power of a wizard into a blast of the arcane power.<br>
<br>
In this 'funnel' I could imagine a base for an imense amount of damage at one time. I'm not talking about a 5% increase above mages DD but a 30% or more increase. This funnel of power from a wizard should start early and have effects that step up with experience.<br>
<br>
I just see that my hit points and my stamina are near always maxed. If they're not I'm already dead. Why not have a line of spells that detracted from health and mana. Or stamina and mana. This way a cleric/healing class could help your recovery time immediately and wizards wouldn't have to sit on their ass so long. <br>
<br>
See where I'm going here? As you cast repeatedly say a cleric healed you and a tank protected you with his 'super taunt' you could 'almost' keep dumping nukes one after the other. So, just whipping up some numbers lets look at the Bane series... say instead of 450mana to cast its 100mana 200health 200 stamina 2000damage? After say 6-7 casts of it you'd still have 3/4 of a mana bar remaining but would be down to like 20-40% health.. cleric heals... continue the dump of the bane spells.<br>
<br>
I realize that this is much to radical of an idea to ever be considered and probably will get some flak from a number of my fellow wizards. I feel this 'could' make us a LOT more group friendly and make us so much more effective. Strategy would also become just as key for even low aggro spells would cause agro and overburns would be only when the party was in dire need.<br>
<br>
There is my manifesto. Thanks for reading and although I haven’t given up on my ‘Raistlin’ I’ve just started Caremon (again sorry if misspelled) <br>
<br>
Keep fighting wizards….<br>
<br>
-Vort<br>
